# Spec File Guardrails

## Hard Blocks (generation fails if violated)

- No `sharedPage.locator(...)` — use POM methods via `pages.<getter>.<method>()`
- No `sharedPage.evaluate()` with DOM guessing — use Playwright built-in methods
- No `force: true` — fix the root cause (wait for element, dismiss overlay)
- No `page.waitForTimeout(number)` — use `commonReusables.waitForAllLoadStates(sharedPage)`
- No fabricated element IDs — all locators must come from app source or existing POM

## Assertion Rules

- No hardcoded strings in `.toBe()`, `.toContain()`, `.toEqual()`, `.toMatch()`, `.toHaveText()` — use global constants
- No `expect.soft(...).toBeTruthy()` for value checks — use `.toBe()` / `.toContain()` with exact values
- Steps mentioning "hard assertion" must use `expect()`, not `expect.soft()`
- Verify steps must have at least one `expect()` call

## Data Rules

- Rates, amounts, miles, invoice numbers must use `testData.*` from CSV — never hardcoded
- Timeout values must use `WAIT.*` constants from `globalConstants.ts`
